{"title":"USA gravel races 2023: Race dates, routes, TV coverage, past winners and how to enter","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/us-gravel-races-dates-routes-tv-enter","date":1682095800000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/us-gravel-races-dates-routes-tv-enter\">USA gravel races 2023: Race dates, routes, TV coverage, past winners and how to enter</a></p>\n<p>Somehow gravel is still growing, with more interested riders, new tech and new routes discovered all the time. The professional scene is also on a consistent upwards trajectory with races in its spiritual home of the USA growing in stature every year.</p>\n<p>With the UCI deciding the time is right to try to take on gravel racing, the less regulated American races are looking to cement their place as the discipline’s true pinnacle. However given its lack of TV coverage, it’s not an easy sport to follow outside of being there, so we’ve compiled a list of some of the biggest American gravel races to add to your calendars.</p>\n<p>Whether you want to keep up with the who’s who of gravel, look for ride inspiration or enter the races yourselves, there are plenty of opportunities throughout the year to get your fix.</p>\n<p>It’s also a good place to start to follow race results to get to know who the big talents in gravel are with riders that you may not see in other disciplines or familiar faces from road races.</p>\n<h2>When does a ride become a race?</h2>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-970x647.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023848/dirty_kanza_05.jpg 2000w\" alt=\"dirty_kanza_05\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><em>Photo: Mike Swim</em></p>\n<p>Most of these events call themselves rides, and that’s because of the emphasis on enjoyment and participation over competition. For amateurs that is most certainly the case, but for the pros it is long, hard racing. In this list we’ve tried to gather the races where the biggest professional gravel racers will be competing. There are ways for anyone to enter most of these races however, whether in their full form or a shorter length version, and whether you ride or race is up to you.</p>\n<p>The biggest series of races to look out for are those part of the Life Time Grand Prix, which is essentially the (non-UCI) Gravel World Cup, with six races throughout the year, a general classification and gravel’s heftiest prize fund. There is also a documentary series about the 2022 Life Time Grand Prix <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@LifeTimeGrandPrix/videos\" target=\"_blank\">available to watch for free on YouTube</a>.</p>\n<p>You’ll also hear a lot about the ‘spirit of gravel’, which refers to the unwritten rules of these rides and their supposedly more laidback and welcoming environment but is often debated and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/spiritofgravel/?hl=en-gb\" target=\"_blank\">heavily memed</a>.</p>\n<h2>2023 US gravel races: Key events for pros, route information, 2022 winners and how to enter</h2>\n<h3>At a glance</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#belgianwaffleridearizona\">Belgian Waffle Ride Arizona</a>, 4th March 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#themidsouth\">The Mid South</a>, 11th March 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#seaotterclassic\">Sea Otter Classic</a>, 23rd April 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#belgianwaffleridecalifornia\">Belgian Waffle Ride California</a>, 16th April 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#gravellocostexas\">Gravel Locos Texas</a>, 20th May 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#belgianwaffleridecanada\">Belgian Waffle Ride Canada</a>, 28th May 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#unboundgravel\">Unbound Gravel</a>, 3rd June 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#belgianwaffleridenorthcarolina\">Belgian Waffle Ride North Carolina</a>, June 2023</strong></li>\n<li><a href=\"#crusherinthetushar\"><strong>Crusher in the Tushar</strong></a><strong>, 8th July 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#leadville\">Leadville Trail 100 MTB</a>, 12th August 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#sbtgrvl\">SBT GRVL</a>, 20th August 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#gravelworlds\">Gravel Worlds</a>, 26th August 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#rebeccasprivateidaho\">Rebecca’s Private Idaho</a>, August/September 2023<br /></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#chequamegon\">Chequamegon MTB Festival</a>, 16th September 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#gravellocoscolorado\">Gravel Locos Colorado</a>, 30th September 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#belgianwaffleridekansas\">Belgian Waffle Ride Kansas</a>, October 2023</strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"#bigsugargravel\">Big Sugar Gravel</a>, 21nd October 2023</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><a></a>Belgian Waffle Ride Arizona</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-970x537.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-970x537.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-300x166.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-768x426.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-750x416.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona-1140x632.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_arizona.png 1312w\" alt width=\"970\" height=\"537\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>The first race of the ever-expanding Belgian Waffle Ride series is new to 2023, but much like the other BWR events – introduced pre ‘gravel’, inspired by the Belgian spring Classics with a mix of tarmac and rough surfaces – it will feature loads of climbing and a multitude of technical challenges through the desert.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>5th March 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where: </strong>Scottsdale, Arizona</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>123 miles, 8,500ft elevation.</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances: </strong>Wafer Ride, 79 miles; Wanna Ride, 40 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://belgianwaffleride.bike/pages/belgian-waffle-ride-az\" target=\"_blank\">belgianwaffleride.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>The Mid South</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-970x970.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-970x970.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-75x75.jpeg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-350x350.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-750x750.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel-1140x1140.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023852/the_mid_south_gravel.jpeg 1440w\" alt=\"the_mid_south_gravel\" width=\"970\" height=\"970\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>100-mile race on red dirt roads – that becomes thick ‘peanut butter mud’ in the wet – with over 5,000ft of elevation.</p>\n<p><strong>When:</strong> 11th March 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Stillwater, Oklahoma</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong><br /></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Cole Paton, Lauren De Crescenzo</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> 12 miles, 50 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.midsouthgravel.com/\" target=\"_blank\">midsouthgravel.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Sea Otter Classic</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-970x647.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023855/sea_otter_classic_race.jpeg 2048w\" alt=\"sea_otter_classic_race\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><em>Photo: Nikki Ritcher</em></p>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>80km ‘Fuego’ XC mountain bike race, two laps of course featuring mixture of gravel, singletrack and sand, with over 5,700ft of elevation. First event of the Life Time Grand Prix series and part of bigger Sea Otter Classic festival featuring heaps of new bike tech.</p>\n<p><strong>When:</strong> 23rd April 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Monterey, California</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Higlights: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/VFNwodFvvSc\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Keegan Swenson, Mo Wilson</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances: </strong>6km (juniors), 40km. Also 25-mile <em>La Gravilla </em>gravel race, road races and other MTB disciplines.</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.seaotterclassic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">seaotterclassic.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Belgian Waffle Ride California</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-970x647.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-768x513.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-750x501.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-1140x761.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023859/belgian_waffle_ride_california.jpeg 1200w\" alt=\"belgian_waffle_ride_california\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>131.7-mile ride with 19 off-road sectors of singletrack, sandy trails and Cali-cobbles that make up 50 miles making it the ‘Hell of the West’. Over 11,000ft of climbing including ten Ardennes-style categorised climbs and a steepest gradient of 23%. Full course details in the BWR <a href=\"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/3154/6181/files/bwr_bijble_ca_2022_r7.pdf?v=1651172491\" target=\"_blank\">Bijbel</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>16th April 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> San Marcos, California</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-970x455.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-970x455.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-300x141.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-768x360.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-1536x721.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-750x352.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route-1140x535.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023902/belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route.png 1862w\" alt=\"belgian_waffle_ride_california_2022_route\" width=\"970\" height=\"455\" /></div>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Alexey Vermeulen, Mo Wilson</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> 71-mile Wafer ride, 37.5-mile Wanna ride</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://belgianwaffleride.bike/pages/california\" target=\"_blank\">belgianwaffleride.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Gravel Locos Texas</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-970x970.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-970x970.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-75x75.jpeg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-350x350.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-750x750.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas-1140x1140.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023906/gravel_locos_texas.jpeg 1440w\" alt=\"gravel_locos_texas\" width=\"970\" height=\"970\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>155.3-mile race with 112 miles of gravel and over 8,200ft of elevation. Rolling hills, river crossings and scenery including old pecan plantations and the Leon River valley.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>20th May 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Hico, Texas</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>157 miles, 6,705ft elevation</p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Laurens ten Dam, Emily Newsom</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> GL100 La Gran 110.2 miles, GL60 La Mediana 69 miles, GL30 La Pequeña 32.8 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.gravellocos.bike/hico\" target=\"_blank\">gravellocos.bike/hico</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Belgian Waffle Ride Canada</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_canada.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_canada.png 746w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/belgian_waffle_ride_canada-300x181.png 300w\" alt width=\"746\" height=\"449\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>A second new Belgian Waffle Ride for 2023 and yes, this is not in the USA, but it’s close enough for us. Details to be announced.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>28th May 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where: </strong>Vancouver Island, British Colombia</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>TBA, 137 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances: </strong>TBA</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://belgianwaffleride.bike/pages/belgian-waffle-ride-bc\" target=\"_blank\">belgianwaffleride.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Unbound Gravel</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-970x647.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-1536x1025.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023909/dirty_kanza_01.jpg 2000w\" alt=\"dirty_kanza_01\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><em>Photo: Mike Swim</em></p>\n<p><strong>What:</strong> The biggest race in gravel. Unbound features 200 miles of the hardest gravel through the rolling flint hills of Kansas, which can become a mudfest. The second race of the Life Time Grand Prix series.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>3rd June 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Emporia, Kansas</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>TBA</p>\n<p><strong>Highlights: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/KW6v2kpDw6g\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Ivar Slik, Sofia Gómez Villafane</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> Junior, 20 miles, 50 miles, 100 miles or the XL 350 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.unboundgravel.com/\" target=\"_blank\">unboundgravel.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Belgian Waffle Ride North Carolina</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-970x541.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-970x541.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-300x167.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-768x428.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-750x418.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina-1140x636.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023913/belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina.png 1180w\" alt=\"belgian_waffle_ride_north_carolina\" width=\"970\" height=\"541\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>The fourth race in the Belgian Waffle Ride series after the additions of Arizona and Canada for 2023, ‘the Hell of the East’, is headlined by the 129.5-mile, 207.4km ride in the Blue Ridge Mountains. Taking in over 13,000ft of climbing and over 52 miles off-road, it’s seen as the hardest in the BWR series. Featuring ‘unroads’, sandy trails, singletrack, mud and water crossings in often hot, humid and windy conditions, makes it a real test – but a scenic one.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>10th June 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Hendersonville, North Carolina</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong> <a href=\"https://ridewithgps.com/routes/39550417\" target=\"_blank\">ridewithgps.com</a></p>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-970x692.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-970x692.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-300x214.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-768x548.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-120x86.png 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-350x250.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-750x535.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-1140x813.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route-190x136.png 190w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023919/belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route.png 1266w\" alt=\"belgian_waffle_ride_nc_2022_route\" width=\"970\" height=\"692\" /></div>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Peter Stetina, Sarah Max</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> Wafer ride 71 miles, Wanna ride 37.5 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://belgianwaffleride.bike/pages/northcarolina\" target=\"_blank\">belgianwaffleride.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Crusher in the Tushar</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-970x649.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-970x649.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-300x201.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-768x514.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-750x502.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-1140x763.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023922/crusher-in-the-tushar_image.jpeg 1400w\" alt=\"crusher-in-the-tushar_image\" width=\"970\" height=\"649\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>A 69.9-mile route that’s 60/40 gravel and tarmac but navigates over 12,000ft of elevation through The Tushars mountain range and Fishlake National Forest. It’s the next race in the Life Time Grand Prix series.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>8th July 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Beaver, Utah</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-970x750.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-970x750.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-300x232.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-768x593.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-1536x1187.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-750x580.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map-1140x881.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023925/crusher_in_the_tushar_map.jpeg 1650w\" alt=\"crusher_in_the_tushar_map\" width=\"970\" height=\"750\" /></div>\n<p><strong>Highlights: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/54pU-WEZsfE\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Keegan Swenson, Haley Smith</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://tusharcrusher.com/\" target=\"_blank\">tucharcrusher.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Leadville Trail 100 MTB</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023929/leadville_100_mtb-970x612.jpeg\" alt=\"leadville_100_mtb\" width=\"970\" height=\"612\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>High altitude mountain bike race in the Rocky Mountains of Colorado, starting at 10,152ft (3,094m) and going up to 12,424ft (3,787m) the Leadville 100 is breathtaking. An out-and-back route, riders head through forest rough service roads, two-track roads and a bit of singletrack. The next part of the Life Time series, it is an offshoot of the Leadville 100 ultramarathon.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>12th August 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Leadville, Colorado</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Highlights: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/3nE4fitBVY4\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Keegan Swenson, Hannah Otto</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> Other Leadville series events spread throughout the year</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.leadvilleraceseries.com/mtb/leadvilletrail100mtb/\" target=\"_blank\">leadvilleraceseries.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>SBT GRVL</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-970x647.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023934/sbt_grvl.jpeg 1800w\" alt=\"sbt_grvl\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>142-mile course over two main climbs near skiing town Steamboat Springs, CO – home of Moots – featuring more than 100 miles of gravel and just under 9,200ft (2,800m) of climbing. A tough ask for anyone racing Leadville unless you’re named Keegan Swenson but one of the premier events on the calendar.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>20th August, 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Steamboat Springs, Colorado</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<div> </div>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>TV coverage: </strong><a href=\"https://www.sbtgrvl.com/live\" target=\"_blank\">sbtgrvl.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Keegan Swenson, Lauren De Crescenzo</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> 100-mile ‘Blue’ route, 60-mile ‘Red’ route, 37-mile ‘Green’</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.sbtgrvl.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sbtgrvl.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Gravel Worlds</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-970x647.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023938/gravel_worlds.jpeg 1000w\" alt=\"gravel_worlds\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>Representing the real ‘Spirit of Gravel’, Gravel Worlds is a lighthearted jab at the seriousness of ‘official’ events and came before the UCI event introduced in 2022. Though there’s an emphasis on the grassroots feel and having fun riding with friends and family, the tough 150-mile course with over 10,000ft of elevation is a self-supported race with only water and basic nutrition given at check points. Winners get World Champions jerseys.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>26th August 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Lincoln, Nebraska</p>\n<p><strong>Routes: </strong>Released a week before the event</p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Adam Roberge, Lauren De Crescenzo</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> 300 miles, 75 miles, 50km</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.gravel-worlds.com/\" target=\"_blank\">gravel-worlds.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Rebecca’s Private Idaho</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-970x646.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-1140x759.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023940/rebeccas_private_idaho.jpeg 1333w\" alt=\"rebeccas_private_idaho\" width=\"970\" height=\"646\" /></div>\n<p><em>Photo: Linda Guerrette / Stellar Media</em></p>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>Four-day, three-stage stage race featuring 43.3-mile opener on singletrack and gravel roads, 4.5-mile uphill individual time-trial, optional rest day 20-mile fun ride, and final 102-mile 90% gravel road big finish.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>August/September 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Ketchum, Idaho</p>\n<p><strong>Routes:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.rebeccasprivateidaho.com/queen-stage-race\" target=\"_blank\">rebeccasprivateidaho.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 overall winners:</strong> Griffin Easter, Haley Smith, Sam Hansen</p>\n<p><b>Alternative distances: </b>Individual stages 102 miles ‘Baked Potato’, 56 miles ‘French Fry’, 20 miles ‘Tater Tot’</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.rebeccasprivateidaho.com/\" target=\"_blank\">rebeccasprivateidaho.com</a></p>\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h3><span>Related Posts</span></h3>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-gravel-bike\">Best of the best gravel bikes 2023: Cyclist’s top-rated gravel and adventure bikes</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/our-private-idaho-off-road-in-the-usa\">Our private Idaho: off-road in the USA</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/little-ride-on-the-prairie-dirty-kanza-sportive-review\">Little ride on the prairie: Unbound Gravel sportive review</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h3>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Cycling spring Classics 2023: Race dates, Monuments, cobbles and live TV guide</a>\r\n                       </h3>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n<h3><a></a>Chequamegon MTB Festival</h3>\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-970x970.jpeg\" alt=\"mountain bike rider covered in mud celebrating a victory\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-970x970.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-768x767.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-75x75.jpeg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-350x350.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-750x749.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb-1140x1139.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/04/chequamegon-mtb.jpeg 1440w\" /><figcaption>Chequamegon MTB Festival</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n<p><strong>What: </strong>The next event in the Life Time Grand Prix is a 40-mile mountain bike race that heads through the Chequamegon-Nicolet National Forest in northern Wisconsin over the American Birkebeiner Ski Trail. It totals around 3,300ft of elevation on a technical course, as you’d expect.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>16th September 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where: </strong>Hayward, Wisconsin</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>Age-group and pros have slightly different routes, here’s what the pros rode in 2022</p>\n<div>\n<div></div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Highlights: </strong><a href=\"https://youtu.be/tFnpBNH-Ftg\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners: </strong>Bradyn Lange, Savilia Blunk</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances: </strong>Short &amp; Fat, 16 miles; Little Loggers, 15 minutes continuous loop for kids</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.cheqmtb.com/\" target=\"_blank\">chqmtb.com</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Gravel Locos Colorado</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-970x970.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-970x970.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-300x300.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-150x150.jpeg 150w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-768x768.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-75x75.jpeg 75w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-350x350.jpeg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-750x750.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado-1140x1140.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03023950/gravel_locos_colorado.jpeg 1440w\" alt=\"gravel_locos_colorado\" width=\"970\" height=\"970\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>New for 2022 is this 170.1-mile route on rural and farm roads in Pueblo, Colorado. With 13,242ft (4,036m) of elevation, it certainly won’t be an easy course but organisers have described the local groads as among the best gravel routes they’ve seen.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>30th September 2022</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Pueblo, Colorado</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>142.7 miles, 10,364ft elevation</p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners: </strong>Russell Finsterwald, Flavia Oliveira Parks</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> La Gran Piedra 105.3 miles, La Mediana 64.8 miles, La Pequeña 30.2 miles (non-timed)</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.gravellocos.bike/pueblo\" target=\"_blank\">gravellocos.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Belgian Waffle Ride Kansas</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-970x545.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-970x545.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-300x169.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-768x432.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-1536x863.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-2048x1151.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-750x422.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024008/cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas-1140x641.png 1140w\" alt=\"cattaneo_belgian_waffle_ride_kansas\" width=\"970\" height=\"545\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>The final BWR of the year and the fourth part of the ‘Quadruple Crown of Gravel’ awarded to the best performers across the Belgian Waffle Ride races excluding Michigan, the Kansas ride is getting longer for 2022 and last year’s course was 86% off-road and had over 8,000ft (2,400m) of climbing.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>14th October 2023</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Lawrence, Kansas</p>\n<p><strong>Route: </strong>TBC 123.2 miles</p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Adam Roberge, Rebecca Fahringer</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> Wafer 76.4 miles, Wanna 39 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://belgianwaffleride.bike/pages/kansas\" target=\"_blank\">belgianwaffleride.bike</a></p>\n<h3><a></a>Big Sugar Gravel</h3>\n<div><img src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-970x647.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2022/06/03024018/big_sugar_gravel-465x310.jpeg 465w\" alt=\"big_sugar_gravel\" width=\"970\" height=\"647\" /></div>\n<p><strong>What: </strong>The final race in the Life Time series, Big Sugar is approx. 100 miles of largely unmaintained gravel, so expect big, loose rocks as well as water crossings with over 6,000ft (1,800m) of elevation gain. Named for Arkansas’s Sugar Creek, riders climb through the Ozark mountains and cross over the state’s northern border with Missouri, not far from Oklahoma, spending half the race outside Arkansas before looping back.</p>\n<p><strong>When: </strong>21st October 2022</p>\n<p><strong>Where:</strong> Bentonville, Arkansas</p>\n<p><strong>Route:</strong></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong> <a href=\"https://youtu.be/nyI_hppkhqY\" target=\"_blank\">Life Time Grand Prix YouTube</a></p>\n<p><strong>2022 winners:</strong> Russell Finsterwald, Paige Onweller</p>\n<p><strong>Alternative distances:</strong> Little Sugar 50 miles</p>\n<p><strong>Enter: </strong><a href=\"https://www.bigsugargravel.com/\" target=\"_blank\">bigsugargravel.com</a></p>\n<p><em>Photos from race organisers unless stated otherwise.</em></p>\n<p><em>For more on gravel rides, bikes and tech, visit our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/felt-breed-carbon-gravel\" target=\"_blank\">gravel hub page</a>.</em></p><p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/us-gravel-races-dates-routes-tv-enter\">USA gravel races 2023: Race dates, routes, TV coverage, past winners and how to enter</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Will Strickson &#124; Deputy Website Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"d586afd13542c0ef65069efd4a54da517694d0750773824c3fdc382bd0ff606e","category":"Cycling"}